$(1)$ Find the standard equation of the ellipse $C$; 
$(2)$ If a line $n$ with slope $k(k\neq 0)$ intersects the ellipse $C$ at points $A$ and $B$, and the slopes $k_{OA}$, $k$, $k_{OB}$ form an arithmetic sequence, and given point $M(1,1)$, 
find the area of $\triangle ABM$ (express the result in terms of $k$); 
$(3)$ Find the maximum value of the area of $\triangle ABM$ from part $(2)$.

